---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout>
<!-- HERO SECTION -->
    <section class="hero-section">
      <div class="hero-content">
        <p class="hero-eyebrow">Your Path Forward</p>
        <h1>Your Journey to Wellness</h1>
        <p class="hero-lead">
          A first consultation is meant to reduce confusion, not add to it.
          Here's exactly what to expect at every step of your journey with us.
        </p>
        <div class="hero-cta">
          <a href="/book.html" class="button-primary">Start Your Journey</a>
          <a href="/faq.html" class="button-outline">Common Questions</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-image">
        <img src="res/mind-grace-entry-n-reception.jpg" alt="Welcoming reception area at Mind Grace Clinic" loading="lazy"/>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- STEP-BY-STEP PROCESS -->
    <section class="section-padded">
      <div class="container-narrow">
        <div class="section-header-center">
          <span class="section-badge">The Process</span>
          <h2>Five Steps to Clarity and Care</h2>
          <p class="section-intro">
            Many people arrive worried about being rushed, judged, or pushed into treatment too quickly.
            Our process is designed to be transparent, collaborative, and paced to your comfort.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="process-timeline">
          <!-- Step 1 -->
          <div class="process-step">
            <div class="step-number">01</div>
            <div class="step-content">
              <h3>Make Contact</h3>
              <p>Reach out by phone, WhatsApp, email, or our booking form. If you're unsure which route fits your situation, our team can help you decide the best way forward.</p>
              <ul class="check-list">
                <li>No special preparation needed</li>
                <li>Bring existing prescriptions or reports if available (optional)</li>
                <li>We'll guide you through next steps</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Step 2 -->
          <div class="process-step">
            <div class="step-number">02</div>
            <div class="step-content">
              <h3>First Consultation</h3>
              <p>Allow around 45 minutes for a comprehensive first consultation so the discussion doesn't feel rushed. The conversation begins with what has been troubling you and how long it has affected daily life.</p>
              <ul class="check-list">
                <li>Discussion of sleep, mood, concentration, stress patterns</li>
                <li>Family context and past treatment history</li>
                <li>For children: development, speech, school concerns, parent observations</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Step 3 -->
          <div class="process-step">
            <div class="step-number">03</div>
            <div class="step-content">
              <h3>Assessment & Understanding</h3>
              <p>The aim is to understand your pattern clearly and explain findings in plain language. You won't be rushed into decisions or overwhelmed with technical terms.</p>
              <ul class="check-list">
                <li>Clear explanation of what we've understood</li>
                <li>Discussion of possible diagnoses (if applicable)</li>
                <li>Time for your questions and concerns</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Step 4 -->
          <div class="process-step">
            <div class="step-number">04</div>
            <div class="step-content">
              <h3>Treatment Planning</h3>
              <p>Together, we create a personalized plan that may include medication, therapy, lifestyle adjustments, or further assessment—whatever serves your needs best.</p>
              <ul class="check-list">
                <li>Medication discussed only when appropriate</li>
                <li>Therapy options explained clearly</li>
                <li>Practical routines and self-care strategies</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>

          <!-- Step 5 -->
          <div class="process-step">
            <div class="step-number">05</div>
            <div class="step-content">
              <h3>Ongoing Care & Follow-up</h3>
              <p>You'll leave with clarity about next steps, whether that's scheduling follow-ups, starting therapy, beginning medication, or focusing on lifestyle changes first.</p>
              <ul class="check-list">
                <li>Clear follow-up schedule</li>
                <li>Access to support between visits</li>
                <li>Adjustments as needed based on progress</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- FAQ SECTION -->
    <section class="section-padded bg-soft">
      <div class="container-narrow">
        <div class="section-header-center">
          <span class="section-badge">Questions</span>
          <h2>Common Questions Before Your First Visit</h2>
        </div>

        <div class="accordion">
          <div class="accordion-item">
            <button class="accordion-trigger" type="button" data-accordion-trigger aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faq-process-1">
              <span class="accordion-title">Do I need a diagnosis before I book?</span>
              <span class="accordion-icon" aria-hidden="true">+</span>
            </button>
            <div class="accordion-panel" id="faq-process-1" hidden>
              <p>No. You can start with what you are experiencing. Many people come without any prior diagnosis—we'll work together to understand what's happening and what might help.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="accordion-item">
            <button class="accordion-trigger" type="button" data-accordion-trigger aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faq-process-2">
              <span class="accordion-title">Will I be judged for what I say?</span>
              <span class="accordion-icon" aria-hidden="true">+</span>
            </button>
            <div class="accordion-panel" id="faq-process-2" hidden>
              <p>The consultation is meant to be calm, respectful, and practical. The goal is understanding and support, not blame. Everything shared is confidential within ethical guidelines.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="accordion-item">
            <button class="accordion-trigger" type="button" data-accordion-trigger aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faq-process-3">
              <span class="accordion-title">Will I definitely be given medicine?</span>
              <span class="accordion-icon" aria-hidden="true">+</span>
            </button>
            <div class="accordion-panel" id="faq-process-3" hidden>
              <p>Not always. Medication is considered when appropriate, alongside practical and therapeutic options. Some concerns respond well to therapy or lifestyle changes alone.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="accordion-item">
            <button class="accordion-trigger" type="button" data-accordion-trigger aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faq-process-4">
              <span class="accordion-title">Can a parent come along for a child or adolescent visit?</span>
              <span class="accordion-icon" aria-hidden="true">+</span>
            </button>
            <div class="accordion-panel" id="faq-process-4" hidden>
              <p>Yes. Parent observations are often important, especially for development, behaviour, and school concerns. For adolescents, part of the session may be private to build trust.</p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="accordion-item">
            <button class="accordion-trigger" type="button" data-accordion-trigger aria-expanded="false" aria-controls="faq-process-5">
              <span class="accordion-title">What if I'm not ready to say everything in the first visit?</span>
              <span class="accordion-icon" aria-hidden="true">+</span>
            </button>
            <div class="accordion-panel" id="faq-process-5" hidden>
              <p>That is okay. The pace can be adjusted. A first consultation does not require you to say everything at once. Trust builds over time, and we respect your readiness.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="section-cta-center">
          <a href="/faq.html" class="button-ghost">View Full FAQ →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- CTA SECTION -->
    <section class="section-padded bg-dark text-light">
      <div class="container-narrow text-center">
        <h2>Ready to Take the First Step?</h2>
        <p class="lead">
          You should leave with more clarity than you came in with. That's our promise.
        </p>
        <div class="cta-group">
          <a href="/book.html" class="button-primary button-large">Request an Appointment</a>
          <a href="/contact.html" class="button-outline button-large">Contact Us</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>
</BaseLayout>
